reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:57:    "post-gap report grammar mystical experience memory inference"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:63:      "overlap": "Very close. Thompson analyzes the waking sleep report as memory versus inference, compares Advaita and Nyaya, discusses the I in the report, and asks whether awareness or minimal selfhood is required across the gap.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:69:      "overlap": "Close. The study uses micro-phenomenological interviews on objectless awareness during sleep, notes limits of reportability, and explicitly raises whether the reporting I is added in memory rather than present during the state.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:94:    "Test clear-light sleep and objectless-awareness reports as the anomaly class, using micro-phenomenological interview methods and serial awakening literature.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:98:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.71 to about 0.58. The cross-tradition admissibility rubric is useful, but the report grammar of dreamless sleep, memory, inference, witness, and post-hoc self attribution has close prior art.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:101:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the distinction is already standard as pramana, memory versus inference, fruition review, teacher verification, or adab of remembrance, and that the new labels do not change practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:123:    "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact source that classifies Advaita, Buddhist, Daoist, and Sufi post-gap reports by subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, and relation. But Evan Thompson's Open MIND essay gives a very close Advaita versus Nyaya analysis of the report I slept peacefully and I did not know anything, including memory, inference, minimal selfhood, and retrospective awareness. Alcaraz-Sanchez's micro-phenomenological study also directly studies reportability, pronoun use, and possible post-hoc self attribution in objectless sleep reports.",
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:11:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:15:Codex residue policy asks what remains. Claude's inferential gap asks what the remainder licenses. Claude's reflexivity policy asks what a method does when it meets itself. Custody policy asks what carries action after the owner is removed. It turns a metaphysical comparison into a practice-ethical variable and extends the interface invariant by focusing on agency, not only identity or awareness.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:24:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:55:- Test the rubric on practice instructions by asking what a teacher tells the practitioner immediately after de-identification, forgetting, surrender, or cessation.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:56:- Compare dual-trained practitioner reports: after agency quiets, does action feel witnessed, ownerless, spontaneous, divine, time-bound, or sourced in unity?
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:57:- Add a protocol improvement: after applying any attention method, ask which human function would become unstable if the method succeeded too well: agency, ethics, memory, care, or language.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:20:- The model predicts that traditions train a post-negation custody rule, not only a doctrine of self or no-self.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:30:Secondary literature gap: I did not find the exact phrase or structure of attention custody across Buddhist no-self, Advaita witness, and Christian apophatic prayer. However, close prior work already distinguishes common mystical experience, culturally shaped interpretation, monistic versus theistic typologies, witness-consciousness, and pure awareness. The originality is therefore a reframing of a known comparison around practice-level ownership language, not a standalone discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:57:Candidate: Dzogchen or Mahamudra luminous selfless awareness, plus Pseudo-Dionysius's claim that the divine Cause is beyond both affirmation and negation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:67:- If: Primary manuals should contain explicit or implicit custody rules near passages that loosen ordinary selfing. Then: Texts should pair negation of objects or self-story with instructions such as do not locate a self, know the unseen seer, or lift the heart to God. Weakens if: The relevant manuals loosen objects without any subsequent owner, Self, or recipient language, or use all three interchangeably. Test surface: Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:75:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:83:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is just the standard experience versus interpretation debate, or say attention is the wrong category and the model misses liberation, ontology, grace, or devotion.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:91:Structural translation: De-identification practices loosen ordinary ownership of thoughts, then assign the released stance to no-self mindfulness, observing self, values, therapist relationship, or a higher power.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:107:- Close-read Dzogchen and Mahamudra instructions on rigpa or luminous awareness against Bahiya and Brihadaranyaka before publishing the custody model.
