reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:44:- Gamma and Metzinger, The Minimal Phenomenal Experience questionnaire, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8279394/: overlap: Close. The MPE-92M factors include wakeful presence, emptiness and non-egoic self-awareness, mental agency, and witness consciousness, which overlap strongly with the proposed interface variables.; difference: The paper is a phenomenological questionnaire and does not make a full cross-tradition convergence theory for spiritual motifs such as wu wei and surrender.; novelty impact: High reduction for the invariant list. Some originality remains in using it as a comparative-audit frame.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:45:- Varela, Thompson, and Rosch, The Embodied Mind, MIT Press overview, https://mitpress.mit.edu/9780262529365/the-embodied-mind/: overlap: Close. Enactivism already reframes cognition as world-disclosure through embodied action and was built in dialogue with Buddhist no-self and mindfulness.; difference: The Interface Invariant Model names a smaller audit-ready set of invariants and compares several traditions rather than building one enactive cognitive-science program.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction. The world-disclosure move is old, but the Lumenary operationalization may be useful.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:50:Unlike Stace, Forman, Katz, Varela, Thompson, Rosch, or Metzinger, this idea proposes a Lumenary comparison unit in which apparent spiritual convergence is scored by recurring changes to attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundary-making, without inferring one shared metaphysical object.
