reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:141:    "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact four-strategy cross-tradition typology that predicts architecture across Buddhism, Advaita, Zen, and Sufism. But the main pressure is heavily precedented in Buddhist personhood debates, Pudgalavada arguments, Collins on selfless persons, Engler on ego strength before no-self, functional-self accounts in Buddhist psychology, and contemporary self-pattern theories of meditation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:154:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Engler, Pudgalavada debates, Collins, or functional-self Buddhist psychology, this idea treats the minimum self as a comparative architecture variable across traditions and claims it predicts effort, verification, warnings, and fruit."
