reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:12:After an objectless or silent state, the first later report is not neutral memory. It is a trained admissibility grammar that assigns evidential weight to the subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, or relation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:16:- Post-gap reports distribute authority instead of simply preserving memory.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:31:Secondary literature gap: I did not find an exact source that classifies Advaita, Buddhist, Daoist, and Sufi post-gap reports by subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, and relation. But Evan Thompson's Open MIND essay gives a very close Advaita versus Nyaya analysis of the report I slept peacefully and I did not know anything, including memory, inference, minimal selfhood, and retrospective awareness. Alcaraz-Sanchez's micro-phenomenological study also directly studies reportability, pronoun use, and possible post-hoc self attribution in objectless sleep reports.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:37:- I slept peacefully and knew nothing memory inference Advaita Nyaya
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:38:- dreamless sleep embodied mind consciousness memory report Advaita Nyaya Thompson
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:39:- objectless awareness sleep report pronoun I memory report micro-phenomenology
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:44:- post-gap report grammar mystical experience memory inference
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:48:- Evan Thompson, Dreamless Sleep, the Embodied Mind, and Consciousness, Open MIND 2015, https://open-mind.net/epubs/dreamless-sleep-the-embodied-mind-and-consciousness-the-relevance-of-a-classical-indian-debate-to-cognitive-science/OEBPS/pt03.html: overlap: Very close. Thompson analyzes the waking sleep report as memory versus inference, compares Advaita and Nyaya, discusses the I in the report, and asks whether awareness or minimal selfhood is required across the gap.; difference: It focuses on the Indian dreamless-sleep debate and cognitive science, not a five-category cross-tradition admissibility rubric spanning cessation, zuowang, and dhikr.; novelty impact: High reduction. The core claim that a gap report has evidential grammar is already present in a sophisticated near-neighbor.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:49:- Alcaraz-Sanchez, Awareness in the Void, Phenomenology and the Cognitive Sciences, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11097-021-09743-0: overlap: Close. The study uses micro-phenomenological interviews on objectless awareness during sleep, notes limits of reportability, and explicitly raises whether the reporting I is added in memory rather than present during the state.; difference: It is empirical-adjacent and sleep-focused, not a comparative doctrinal model of admissibility rules.; novelty impact: High reduction and strong anomaly source. It supports the need for a report grammar but weakens any claim that post-gap grammar is primary evidence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:87:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say the distinction is already standard as pramana, memory versus inference, fruition review, teacher verification, or adab of remembrance, and that the new labels do not change practice.
