reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:97:Prediction: Clinical and legal settings should show different admissibility grammars for blackout reports, anesthesia emergence, trauma memory, and psychedelic ego dissolution, and these grammars should predict what is treated as evidence of continuity, harm, or transformation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.md:107:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.71 to about 0.58. The cross-tradition admissibility rubric is useful, but the report grammar of dreamless sleep, memory, inference, witness, and post-hoc self attribution has close prior art.
