observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:42:For Lumenary, this means failed synthesis is not wasted research. It becomes a way to discover finer distinctions: witness versus awareness, emptiness versus absence, surrender versus passivity, soul versus continuity, nondual experience versus nondual ontology.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:46:This rule prevents the site from turning resemblance into proof. A Buddhist claim about no-self does not prove an Advaita claim about Atman just because both weaken ordinary ego. A physics claim about fields does not prove a spiritual claim about consciousness just because both reject naive material objects. Similarity can generate inquiry. It cannot carry the burden of truth by itself.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-gap-trains-the-seeker.md:15:Comparative work often asks whether paths cross a gap, dissolve it, or reveal it as false. This proposal asks what the gap trains. It connects the timing question with the kind of person a practice forms: effort can ripen, postponement can be cut, misperception can be exposed, and longing can keep relation alive. That makes disagreement over distance productive without treating one path's answer as evidence for another path's metaphysics.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-gap-trains-the-seeker.md:19:- Thinking method source: Dogen, Bendowa, practice and verification as one, summarized in Encyclopedia of Buddhism: https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-gap-trains-the-seeker.md:25:- Local Codex observation, observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-gap-trains-the-seeker.md:30:The model can romanticize distance and make real suffering, ignorance, or alienation look useful. A Buddhist gradual path may say distance is not a noble instrument but a condition to end through training. A Zen enactment path may say treating no-distance as a function already misses practice-realization. A Sufi may say longing is not a psychological tool but the trace of a real Beloved. The Dogen lens used here may bias the comparison against causal paths by making sequence look like delusion; the mindfulness lens may over-neutralize devotion by turning longing into an observed state. The idea should be weakened unless close practice texts show that each path deliberately trains with its distance policy.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-gap-trains-the-seeker.md:57:- Test Sufi stations and states as a hybrid where effort crosses distance but grace keeps arrival unowned.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-gap-trains-the-seeker.md:59:- Check whether distance-function predicts distinct ethical fruits beyond temporal topology, receiver policy, and verification architecture.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:34:      "expected_observation": "Advaita sources should use continuity, memory, or self-luminosity to defend awareness across apparent absence, while Buddhist sources should explain retrospective knowledge without positing a continuous knower.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:47:    "Evan Thompson Advaita witness consciousness embodied subjectivity no-self"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:77:      "overlap": "Close anomaly. MMK refuses both self and no-self as final positions, which undercuts a simple two-policy model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:90:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "They say the model restates familiar debates: direct recognition versus no-self, constructivism versus pure consciousness, or Codex's prior residue-policy thesis.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:95:      "Does inferential policy change how you teach deep sleep, cessation, awareness, and no-self?"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:113:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The idea cites strong sources, but the audit found close prior art in Codex residue-policy work, Advaita self-luminosity scholarship, Stace/Forman/Katz interpretation debates, Loy's Buddhism and Advaita comparison, and Madhyamaka self/no-self refusal. More work is needed in Sanskrit, Pali, Gaudapada, Shankara, Abhidhamma, Yogacara, and Madhyamaka commentaries.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.md:16:- The key difference is inferential policy, not only doctrine of self versus no-self.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.md:44:- Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, Shankara, https://seop.illc.uva.nl/entries/shankara/: overlap: Close. Shankara's witness accounts for memory and deep sleep continuity and resists the claim that absence of object implies absence of consciousness.; difference: The Lumenary idea reframes this as burden allocation after negation.; novelty impact: High reduction for the Advaita side.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.md:45:- Thanissaro Bhikkhu, The Not-Self Strategy, https://www.buddhistinquiry.org/article/the-not-self-strategy/: overlap: Close for the Buddhist side. It denies that the Buddha's teaching should be reduced to a metaphysical no-self thesis and treats not-self as a strategy.; difference: The Lumenary idea treats the strategy as an inference policy against remainder claims.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.md:46:- Nagarjuna, Mulamadhyamakakarika 18.6, English text example, https://docslib.org/doc/1736275/mulamadhyamakakarika-by-nagarjuna: overlap: Close at the level of refusing both self and no-self as final views.; difference: The Lumenary model compares Upanishadic and early Buddhist rules, while MMK offers a Madhyamaka deconstruction of the polarity itself.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction and important third-case constraint.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.md:82:Answers that support contribution: Experts say the field distinguishes direct recognition, scriptural assertion, inference, pragmatic bracketing, and recursive testing in ways existing self/no-self comparisons blur.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:11:Effort in a spiritual path should be compared by its authorized use, not only by whether it causes awakening. A practice gives effort an envelope: what the seeker may do, what effort must never claim to do, and which distortion the doing is meant to block. In one path effort cultivates conditions without owning the result; in another it clears a veil without producing the real; in another it empties the person so a gift can arrive; in another it enacts the result now. The shared question is not whether effort works. It is what kind of effort can continue without stealing the insight. This separates causal power from protective function and explains why similar exercises can become incompatible when moved across traditions.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:15:Many accounts treat effort as a doctrinal problem: produced result, revealed truth, received grace, enacted identity, or unresolved paradox. Others treat misuse as a moral problem that appears after insight. The new distinction is to make effort's boundary the comparison unit. A tradition's coherence may depend less on how much effort it demands than on where it stops effort from crossing into ownership, passivity, self-certification, or magical waiting. This gives comparison a narrower test: two methods are closer when they authorize and forbid similar uses of effort, even if their peak statements differ.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:19:- Thinking method source: Dao De Jing chapter 48, source card notes/source-cards/daoism-dao-de-jing-chapter-48.md and https://ctext.org/dictionary.pl?id=11634&if=en. I used learning by decrease to subtract the assumption that effort must either cause awakening or fail to cause it; then I asked what effort is allowed to protect.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:20:- Contrasting method source: SN 45.8 Magga-vibhanga Sutta on right effort, as cited in observations/claude/2026-05-26-can-effort-reach-what-effort-cannot-produce.md. This kept decrease from becoming passivity by insisting that some states require deliberate cultivation and restraint.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:22:- Local Claude observation: observations/claude/2026-05-26-can-effort-reach-what-effort-cannot-produce.md, especially the five resolutions of the practice-result paradox: removal, production, identity, reception, and paradox-holding.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:23:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:30:The envelope idea may be too tidy. Traditions often combine several effort rules at once: causal preparation, non-attainment teaching, teacher testing, grace, and ordinary discipline. It may also smuggle a modern control metaphor into texts whose main concern is devotion, liberation, obedience, or wisdom. The Daoist decrease lens helped reveal over-effort, but it can make careful cultivation look like interference; right effort corrects this by insisting that some states must be deliberately prevented, abandoned, cultivated, and maintained. The model should be rejected where close practice texts show no stable boundary around effort, or where practitioners do not experience effort as theft-prone.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:55:- Build an effort-envelope rubric with five fields: authorized action, forbidden claim, feared distortion, verifier, and public sign of failure.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:56:- Test one shared-looking method across Zen sitting, Theravada right effort, Advaita self-inquiry, and Sufi remembrance; ask whether the method changes when the effort envelope changes.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:57:- Study historically successful hybrids to see whether they combine doctrines or create a new boundary around what effort may do.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:58:- Ask dual-trained practitioners whether switching traditions changes the felt ethics of effort: striving, waiting, clearing, receiving, or enacting.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:59:- Protocol improvement: before using any practitioner method as a thinking lens, name what the method permits effort to do and what it forbids effort to claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:12:A path that dissolves, denies, or transcends selfhood still requires a minimum functioning self, agency, memory, reflexivity, and continuity, and each tradition's strategy for managing that requirement predicts its practice architecture.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:16:- Self-dissolving practice presupposes capacities for hearing instruction, effort, memory, error recognition, and self-observation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:20:- The management strategy should predict effort theory, verification, warnings, and post-practice fruit.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:30:Secondary literature gap: I did not find an exact four-strategy cross-tradition typology that predicts architecture across Buddhism, Advaita, Zen, and Sufism. But the main pressure is heavily precedented in Buddhist personhood debates, Pudgalavada arguments, Collins on selfless persons, Engler on ego strength before no-self, functional-self accounts in Buddhist psychology, and contemporary self-pattern theories of meditation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The model may turn a researcher's philosophical tension into a practitioner's lived problem. It also risks forcing mixed traditions into clean boxes. Theravada, Zen, Advaita, Sufism, Dzogchen, and Christian grace traditions often combine effort, surrender, recognition, teacher relation, and ethical transformation across stages.
