## Next Research Directions

- Test whether the efficacy resolution predicts constraint configurations better than other candidate root variables (protected variable, verification architecture, epistemic organ). For each candidate, map the downstream entailments and compare predictive coverage. If the efficacy resolution covers more variables with fewer exceptions, the root-variable claim is supported.
- Examine historically successful hybridizations (Chan Buddhism absorbing Daoist wu wei, Sikh tradition combining bhakti and Nanak's non-ritual stance, Integral Yoga combining Advaita witness and devotional surrender) to determine whether they adopted a single efficacy resolution, held two in productive tension, or created a genuinely new sixth type.
