reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:57:Candidate: Dzogchen or Mahamudra luminous selfless awareness, plus Pseudo-Dionysius's claim that the divine Cause is beyond both affirmation and negation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:67:- If: Primary manuals should contain explicit or implicit custody rules near passages that loosen ordinary selfing. Then: Texts should pair negation of objects or self-story with instructions such as do not locate a self, know the unseen seer, or lift the heart to God. Weakens if: The relevant manuals loosen objects without any subsequent owner, Self, or recipient language, or use all three interchangeably. Test surface: Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:75:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:83:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is just the standard experience versus interpretation debate, or say attention is the wrong category and the model misses liberation, ontology, grace, or devotion.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:107:- Close-read Dzogchen and Mahamudra instructions on rigpa or luminous awareness against Bahiya and Brihadaranyaka before publishing the custody model.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:15:Codex residue policy asks what remains. Claude's inferential gap asks what the remainder licenses. Claude's reflexivity policy asks what a method does when it meets itself. Custody policy asks what carries action after the owner is removed. It turns a metaphysical comparison into a practice-ethical variable and extends the interface invariant by focusing on agency, not only identity or awareness.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:56:- Compare dual-trained practitioner reports: after agency quiets, does action feel witnessed, ownerless, spontaneous, divine, time-bound, or sourced in unity?
observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:57:- Add a protocol improvement: after applying any attention method, ask which human function would become unstable if the method succeeded too well: agency, ethics, memory, care, or language.
sources/sources_index.jsonl:20:{"created_at": "2026-05-25T15:47:54-07:00", "notes": "Scientific model connecting interoceptive prediction, agency, and presence. Useful for Lumenary's remainder-pressure idea as empirical-adjacent grounding.", "path": null, "source_id": "consciousness-science-an-interoceptive-predictive-coding-model-of-conscious-presence", "source_type": "paper", "title": "An Interoceptive Predictive Coding Model of Conscious Presence", "tradition": "consciousness-science", "url": "https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3254200/"}
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice-d80ea45da8d6d4ca.json:20:    "prediction": "Therapies that strengthen observer-self language should differ from therapies that deconstruct observer-self language in how clients report agency and identity after decentering.",
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:11:Some spiritual distance is a guardrail, not a defect. A path may keep a gap between knower and known because closing it too quickly turns insight into possession. Gradual training uses distance to make effort honest. Practice-realization denies distance so life is not postponed. Recognition paths dissolve distance when it is only misreading. But devotional, relational, Daoist, and some Buddhist practices preserve a different kind of distance: not separation from truth, but protection from grasping. The beloved must not become an object, the other must not become a concept, the situation must not become the will's project, and an arising feeling must not become mine. Cross-tradition comparison should therefore ask a new question before deciding whether a gap is real: what would be harmed if this gap vanished?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Theistic surrender and grace traditions, for example Christian apophatic prayer or Islamic tawakkul, may treat relation to God as irreducible, not as de-emphasis of agency or boundary-making.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.json:11:    "The shared structure is the human interface of attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundaries.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.json:20:    "structural_translation": "Interface invariants become attention routing, agency attribution, salience marking, avatar identity, and boundary control.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.json:21:    "would_count_against_it": "Altering interface variables changes task performance but does not produce predictable shifts in self, agency, salience, or boundary reports."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.json:23:  "exact_claim": "Cross-tradition convergence may come from recurring human interface invariants such as attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundary-making, rather than from discovery of the same hidden metaphysical substance.",
