reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.json:118:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Stace, Forman, Katz, Varela, Thompson, Rosch, or Metzinger, this idea proposes a Lumenary comparison unit in which apparent spiritual convergence is scored by recurring changes to attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundary-making, without inferring one shared metaphysical object."
notes/source-cards/consciousness-science-an-interoceptive-predictive-coding-model-of-conscious-presence.md:11:Scientific model connecting interoceptive prediction, agency, and presence. Useful for Lumenary's remainder-pressure idea as empirical-adjacent grounding.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:25:- observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md, observations/codex/2026-05-26-each-path-has-a-different-alarm.md, and observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-interruption-gate.md.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:12:Cross-tradition convergence may come from recurring human interface invariants such as attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundary-making, rather than from discovery of the same hidden metaphysical substance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:17:- The shared structure is the human interface of attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundaries.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:35:- interface invariants attention identity salience agency boundary-making spiritual traditions convergence
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:44:- Gamma and Metzinger, The Minimal Phenomenal Experience questionnaire, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8279394/: overlap: Close. The MPE-92M factors include wakeful presence, emptiness and non-egoic self-awareness, mental agency, and witness consciousness, which overlap strongly with the proposed interface variables.; difference: The paper is a phenomenological questionnaire and does not make a full cross-tradition convergence theory for spiritual motifs such as wu wei and surrender.; novelty impact: High reduction for the invariant list. Some originality remains in using it as a comparative-audit frame.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:46:- Metzinger, Minimal phenomenal experience, https://philpapers.org/rec/METMPE: overlap: Close. Metzinger explicitly studies pure awareness, self-luminosity, sakshin, turiya, rigpa, and minimal phenomenal selfhood as a route to modeling consciousness.; difference: Metzinger is not primarily making a comparative religion publication rule for convergence claims.; novelty impact: High reduction for the consciousness and self-model components.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:50:Unlike Stace, Forman, Katz, Varela, Thompson, Rosch, or Metzinger, this idea proposes a Lumenary comparison unit in which apparent spiritual convergence is scored by recurring changes to attention, identity, salience, agency, and boundary-making, without inferring one shared metaphysical object.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:54:Candidate: Theistic surrender and grace traditions, for example Christian apophatic prayer or Islamic tawakkul, may treat relation to God as irreducible, not as de-emphasis of agency or boundary-making.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:62:- If: Cross-tradition reports of witness, emptiness, surrender, and wu wei should cluster by shifts in attention, agency, salience, identity, and boundary experience even when doctrinal vocabulary differs. Then: Blind coders should reliably tag these interface variables in practitioner reports better than chance, while also preserving doctrinal differences. Weakens if: Reports cluster mainly by tradition-specific doctrine, devotional object, or teacher vocabulary, with weak cross-tradition interface structure. Test surface: Qualitative coding of meditation, prayer, and contemplative-inquiry interviews across Advaita, Theravada, Daoist, Sufi, and Christian sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:63:- If: Low-metaphysical comparison using interface variables should predict practice similarities better than metaphysical labels such as Self, emptiness, God, or nature. Then: Practice instructions with similar attention and agency moves should produce similar near-term phenomenological reports even when ontology differs. Weakens if: Metaphysical training context predicts reports more strongly than interface variables do. Test surface: Matched practitioner interviews before and after narrowly specified practices.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:77:- Do you already compare traditions by shifts in attention, agency, salience, identity, and boundaries?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:89:Structural translation: Interface invariants become attention routing, agency attribution, salience marking, avatar identity, and boundary control.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:93:Would count against it: Altering interface variables changes task performance but does not produce predictable shifts in self, agency, salience, or boundary reports.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:107:- Add a devotional anomaly set: grace, surrender, bhakti, tawakkul, and Christian apophasis.
