reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:51:- Not-Self Sutra, Barre Center for Buddhist Studies, https://www.buddhistinquiry.org/article/not-self-sutra/: overlap: Extremely close for the Buddhist unit. It speaks of functional or enactive self, minimal self, agency without ownership, and discipline through causes and conditions.; difference: It is a contemporary Buddhist exposition rather than a cross-tradition predictive model.; novelty impact: High reduction. Parts of the Lumenary wording risk being a renamed Buddhist functional-self account.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:52:- Pattern Theory of Selflessness, Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-024-02418-2: overlap: Close contemporary theory. It distinguishes minimal self, ownership, agency, self-pattern, and how meditation transforms self-processes toward selflessness.; difference: It is cognitive-scientific and Buddhist-psychological rather than a primary-text comparative architecture model.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction for the minimal-self and practice-transformation language.
